          • [ - ] andrew7taylor - member since 04-Jan-17

            @jefferee - I don't think so; the 4312 brings the best out of the best players perfectly. If Kroos and Modric didn't have a defensive midfielder behind them, they would have to be more defensive themselves and not have as much influence on the game. Isco would have to play on either side, but his strength is moving off the ball and picking it up in unexpected places, and starting from the wing would constrain his ability to do that. There is a reason why only Atlético and Monaco play 442 on the top level. It makes a team lose the battle in the middle of the pitch almost by default against 3 man midfields, so you need to have hard-working, fast players and move the ball with tremendous speed to have any success. But RM have more technique than athleticism across the squad (as most clubs at the top, top level do), and so it wouldn't do them any favours.
